tool.name: GDVSpectra_Threshold

param.name: in_nc_file
param.dialogReference: A GDV Likelihood NetCDF generated by the GDV Likelihood. Requires x, y, time and a Likelihood variable.

param.name: out_nc_file
param.dialogReference: The folder location and filename of the output NetCDF file containing GDV Threshold map.

param.name: in_use_all_dates
param.displayname: Use median of all input Likelihood images
param.dialogReference: Whether or not to use a median of all available GDV Likelihood images within the input GDV Likelihood NetCDF. Can be useful to reduce potential variation from cross-year seasonal influences.

param.name: in_specific_year
param.dialogReference: The specific year to use if a median of all available GDV Likelihood images within the input GDV Likelihood NetCDF is not checked. Only the year set here will be thresholded and included in the output GDV Threshold NetCDF.

param.name: in_occurrence_feat
param.dialogReference:
A feature layer or shapefile of points representing known GDV species locations (occurrences). It is recommended that all point should represent one (or very similar) potential GDV species.

Occurrences points are used to calculate the Receiver Operator Characteristic (ROC) accuracy metric known as the Area Under the Curve (AUC). This is then used to find an optimal GDV Likelihood cut off value to threshold GDV Likelihood.

Note: the feature of shapefile must be projected in GDA 94 Australian Albers (EPSG: 3577).

param.name: in_pa_column
param.displayname: Set field of presence and absence values
param.dialogReference:
The column that holds a value representing presence (1) and absence (0) for each occurrence point. Only enabled if a occurrence feature or shapefile is entered above.

Note: Any other values other than 1 and 0 will be ignored.

param.name: in_std_dev
param.dialogReference: The standard deviation value to threshold GDV Likelihood maps to. Values above this value will be included (i.e., very high GDV Likelihood), and all others will be masked out.

param.name: in_if_nodata
param.dialogReference:
Whether to exclude an occurrence point from the AUC threshold method. Can choose between:

- Any: if a single NoData value is detected, the point is discarded from analysis.

- All: if all values are NoData in the time series, the point is discarded from analysis.

param.name: in_remove_stray
param.dialogReference: Whether to remove salt and pepper (i.e., stray) pixels using a majority filter. For example, if one GDV Likelihood pixel is surrounded by a majority of NoData values, the pixel will be set to NoData.

param.name: in_convert_binary
param.dialogReference: Whether to convert GDV Threshold values to 1 or to keep the original Likelihood values. The former is easier to read but loses some nuance between high and very high Likelihood areas.

param.name: in_add_result_to_map
param.dialogReference: Whether to visualise the results to the currently active map once modelling is complete or not.

tool.summary:
Takes a groundwater dependent vegetation (GDV) likelihood map generated from the GDV Likelihood module and thresholds it into a map of high probability only. Thresholding can be performed based on existing presence and absence points of GDV species or via a standard deviation value. The output is a NetCDF file containing the thresholded GDV Likelihood map for either a single year or for the median of all Likelihood images in the input combined.

See citation: <missing>.
